LAN Device Connection Guidelines:
What is LAN?
A LAN (Local Area Network) connects multiple devices (computers, printers, servers) within a small area like a home, lab,
office, or building using Ethernet or Wi-Fi.

Basic LAN Devices:
Router → Connects LAN to internet and manages IP addresses
Switch → Connects devices inside LAN
Hub → Older/simple LAN device (less efficient)
Ethernet Cable → Physical connection medium
Computers / Printers / Servers → End devices

